---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Masthead from "../components/Masthead.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="Contribute · OpenResearch">
  <main class="max-w-[1080px] mx-auto px-6 pt-8">
    <Masthead active="contribute" />
    <article class="cwrap">
      <h1 class="font-display">Publish in under 15 minutes</h1>
      <p class="lede">Everything on this site is a markdown file merged through a pull request.
        Review works like a journal that publishes first: machines referee before the merge,
        people review in the open after it — and both reviews live on the page.</p>

      <h2 class="caps" style="color: var(--oxblood)">Pick a tier</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>What it is</th><th>Required sections</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><b>Finding</b></td><td>One page, one measured result</td><td>Summary · Context · Technique · Evidence · How to replicate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Technical report</b></td><td>Long-form study</td><td>Abstract · Background · Method · Results · Discussion · How to replicate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Research paper</b></td><td>Full paper with related work and pre-registered metrics</td><td>Abstract · Introduction · Related work · Method · Results · Discussion · Conclusion · How to replicate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Tutorial</b></td><td>Hands-on walkthrough</td><td>You'll need · You'll build · Steps · Wrap-up</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Note</b></td><td>One useful observation</td><td>Freeform, 100+ characters</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="caps" style="color: var(--oxblood)">Stage 1 — before the merge (minutes, fully automated)</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Copy the template from <code>content/templates/&lt;tier&gt;.md</code> into
            <code>content/contributions/&lt;your-slug&gt;/index.md</code> (slug = the <code>id</code> field).
            Add a <code>bundle/</code> with a README if others should be able to replicate it.</li>
        <li><b>Desk check.</b> Run <code>npm run validate</code> — schema, required sections, links.
            This is the only hard gate; CI runs exactly the same checks.</li>
        <li><b>Referee report.</b> The <a href="/toolkit">toolkit's</a> <code>judge</code> writes a
            structured review — <i>Clarity · Claims vs evidence · Reproducibility</i> — as a record
            that publishes with your page. Every axis at <i>adequate</i> or better → your PR merges.</li>
        <li><b>Revisions requested?</b> An axis at <i>needs work</i> pauses the merge. Revise and
            re-run — or <b>publish over the objection</b> with a written reason. The dissenting
            review and your reason appear together on the published page. No silent merges,
            no silent rejections.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="caps" style="color: var(--oxblood)">Stage 2 — after publication (humans, in the open)</h2>
      <p>Publication is where review begins, not where it ends. Anyone can add a signed record
        to someone else's work — all of it renders on the contribution page:</p>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Record</th><th>What it says</th><th>Template</th><th>Arena points</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><b>Review</b></td><td>A structured read: the same three axes the machine referee scores, signed by you</td><td><code>review.yaml</code></td><td>5</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Replication</b></td><td>You ran the bundle and measured — the strongest form of peer review</td><td><code>replication.yaml</code></td><td>12 (author +15)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Adoption</b></td><td>Your team runs it in a real pipeline</td><td><code>adoption.yaml</code></td><td>author +8</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>A page climbs the ladder as evidence lands: <span class="lad">Machine-reviewed</span> →
        <span class="lad">Peer-reviewed</span> → <span class="lad">Verified</span>. The judge earns
        no points — credit is for people.</p>

      <p class="pitch">Reviewing is not a favor here; it is scored, attributed work.
        Your reviews and replications appear on <a href="/arena">the arena</a> and your
        <a href="/browse">public profile</a> — the fastest way to build standing before
        you publish your own first result.</p>
    </article>
    <Footer />
  </main>
</Base>
<style>
  .cwrap { max-width: 68ch; padding-top: 40px; }
  .cwrap h1 { font-weight: 600; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px); margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .lede { font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-weight: 500;
          font-size: 18px; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 28px; }
  .cwrap h2 { margin: 30px 0 12px; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; display: block; overflow-x: auto; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid var(--hairline); padding: 8px 14px; text-align: left; }
  th { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: .12em;
       text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--slate); }
  ol { padding-left: 20px; } li { margin: 8px 0; max-width: 62ch; }
  code { font-family: ui-monospace, Consolas, monospace; font-size: .88em; background: var(--soft);
         border: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 5px; }
  a { color: var(--oxblood); }
  .lad { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: .08em;
         text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--verified); font-weight: 600; }
  .pitch { border-top: 2px solid var(--ink); margin-top: 28px; padding-top: 14px;
           font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-size: 17px; }
</style>
